 with students and staff inside. Vanguard report that 344 female students and staff of Providence High School, Independence Layout, Enugu were detained in the school premises by officials of AMCON. Vanguard News Nigeria By Chinedu Adonu No fewer than 344 female students and staff of Providence High School, Independence layout, Enugu  were Thursday, detained in the  school premises by officials of Assets Management Corporation of Nigeria, AMCON. The AMCON personnel were said to have invaded the school premises and reportedly took possession of… January 22, 2021 In "News" By Chinedu Adonu No fewer than 344 students of Providence High School Enugu are still under confinement by the Asset Management Company of Nigeria, AMCON, as at Monday, January 25, 2021, five days after they locked up the entrances to the school with students and staff inside the premises. The… January 25, 2021 In "Metro" DAYS after, the controversy surrounding No. 17, Awolowo Road, Ikoyi, Lagos, a commercial property that houses a number of businesses, is yet to abate. The Asset Management Corporation of Nigeria, AMCON, had filed a debt recovery action against the property owner for failing to pay back a loan obtained from… November 3, 2016 In "Metro"